#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
#. VAR: Acelakavagga → paṭha­ma­raho­nisaj­ja­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "44. Rahopaṭicchannasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 44: the training rule on private and concealed"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.96"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.44.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.357"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa906"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sahāyakassa gharaṃ gantvā tassa pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappesi."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan went to the house of a friend and sat down with his wife in private on a concealed seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "The husband complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayhaṃ pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda sit in private on a concealed seat with my wife?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa907"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda sit in private on a concealed seat with a woman?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you sit in private on a concealed seat with a woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa908"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk sits down in private on a concealed seat with a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "(<em>44</em>:<strong>93</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.44.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.44.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa909"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa910"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.358"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā, antamaso tadahujātāpi dārikā, pageva mahattarī."
msgstr "a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal; even a girl born on that very day, all the more an older one."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa911"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa912"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Raho nāma"
msgstr "In private:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "cakkhussa raho sotassa raho."
msgstr "there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear."

#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Cakkhussa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the eye:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding."

#. </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Sotassa raho nāma"
msgstr "Private to the ear:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ."
msgstr "one is unable to hear ordinary speech."

#. </span></span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa913"></a> 
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Paṭicchannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A concealed seat:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: kuṭṭena → kuḍḍena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: kotthaḷiyā → kotthaliyā (bj) | koṭṭhaḷiyā (s1-3) | kotthaḷikāya (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "āsanaṃ kuṭṭena vā kavāṭena vā kilañjena vā sāṇipākārena vā rukkhena vā thambhena vā kotthaḷiyā vā, yena kenaci paṭicchannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "it is concealed by a wall, a screen, a door, a screening cloth, a tree, a pillar, a grain container, or anything else."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa914"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti"
msgstr "Sits down:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "mātugāme nisinne bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if the monk sits down or lies down next to a seated woman, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "Bhikkhu nisinne mātugāmo upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If a woman sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.44.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa915"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Mātugāme vematiko raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he is unsure if it is, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.97"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa916"></a>
#. MS reads <i lang="pi">tiracchānagatāya vā manussaviggahitthiyā vā</i>, but it is not clear what <i lang="pi">manussaviggahitthiyā</i> would refer to in this context, and so I take this to be an editing mistake. I here follow the PTS reading, <i lang="pi">tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā</i>, which makes better sense and is consistent with the following rule.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatāya vā manussaviggahitthiyā vā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sits down in private on a concealed seat with a female spirit, with a female ghost, with a sexual nonconformist, or with a female animal in form of a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman,  he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.44.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa917"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "yo koci viññū puriso dutiyo hoti,"
msgstr "if he has a man who understands as a companion;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he stands and does not sit down;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.359"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "arahopekkho,"
msgstr "if he is not seeking privacy;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "aññavihito nisīdati,"
msgstr "if he sits down thinking of something else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa918"></a>
#. VAR: Rahopaṭicchannasikkhāpadaṃ → paṭha­ma­raho­nisaj­ja­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc44:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "Rahopaṭicchannasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on private and concealed, is finished."

